description:
&lt;p&gt;Interested in supporting your local community? Come and join us at AWP Mental Health Trust and become an NHS hero. We are looking for new colleagues, with a passion for helping people, to join us as Healthcare Support Workers in our teams based in Weston Super Mare.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are very proud of our amazing staff, who are continuing to work throughout the COVID19 pandemic, supporting people with mental health issues across the region.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dune Ward, based at Weston General Hospital, which is part of Avon and Wiltshire Mental Health Partnership NHS Trust (AWP), is a 14 bed ward caring for those with a dementia illness for a short period of assessment and treatment whilst they are in hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have a passion and experience with working with people with dementia, are committed to delivering a high standard of care and are committed to team working we would really like to meet you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role requires working a mixture of shifts and weekends (early shifts 07:00-15:00, late shifts 13:30-21:30 and night shifts 21:00-07:30).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working closely with our multi disciplinary teams, supporting service users, you will receive a great induction, training to complete the NHS Care Certificate and a Level 3 Healthcare apprenticeship. If you have some experience of caring work already that would be great – but if not, we will support you to develop the skills and experience needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an NHS employee you will have a wide range of benefits and discounts, the NHS pension scheme and a generous annual leave entitlement. Best of all you will have the reward of doing a job that really matters, with colleagues who care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sarah PaveyJob Ward Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01934 836522 or 01934 836500&lt;/p&gt;
